# Explicit Independent Set Data for C_15^{⊠4}

The 2842 vertices from Appendix B of
"The asymptotic spectrum distance, graph limits, and the Shannon capacity"
(de Boer, Buys, Zuiddam).

## Paper format

The paper lists vertices as 4-character codes using base-15 digits
(0–9, A=10, B=11, C=12, D=13, E=14):

    0018 001A 003B 004D 005B 0061 006E 0082 00A2 00A4 ...

Each code "ABCD" represents the vertex (A, B, C, D) ∈ (ℤ/15ℤ)⁴.

## Encoding here

Each code is stored as the single natural number A·3375 + B·225 + C·15 + D,
i.e. the base-15 interpretation. For example:

    "0018" → 0·3375 + 0·225 + 1·15 + 8 = 23
    "001A" → 0·3375 + 0·225 + 1·15 + 10 = 25
    "EEDC" → 14·3375 + 14·225 + 13·15 + 12 = 50607

The function `decodeVertex` recovers the 4-tuple (A, B, C, D) ∈ (ZMod 15)⁴
from this encoding.
-/
import Mathlib.Data.ZMod.Basic

namespace C15Data

/-- Decode a base-15 encoded natural number to a vertex in (ZMod 15)^4. -/
def decodeVertex (n : ℕ) : Fin 4 → ZMod 15 :=
  fun i => match i with
    | 0 => (n / 3375 : ℕ)
    | 1 => (n / 225 % 15 : ℕ)
    | 2 => (n / 15 % 15 : ℕ)
    | 3 => (n % 15 : ℕ)

